Source: ethtool
Section: utils
Priority: extra
Maintainer: Eric Delaunay <delaunay@debian.org>
Standards-Version: 3.6.2
Build-Depends: debhelper

Package: ethtool
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Conflicts: sparc-utils (<< 1.9-1)
Description: Display or change ethernet card settings
 ethtool is used for querying settings of an ethernet device and changing them.
 .
 Many ethernet drivers in 2.4 or newer kernel can be queried and tuned using
 ethtool.
 .
 However, backward compatibility is ensured on 2.2 kernel running Sparc with
 SUN Happy Meal (hme) Ethernet card.

